snippet.title: Connor Malbeuf
snippet.description:
Connor Malbeuf is a Canadian LA-based comedian, producer and filmmaker. 
Malbeuf's first feature documentary, One Week 'Til Doomsday is coming soon.

When translated from French to English, Malbeuf means bad beef or diseased cattle.
 
A last name like that gives you a green light into one career: comedy.
​
Though born and raised just outside of Toronto, Canada, Connor has gone the American way since 2018. With a Master’s degree from Boston University’s College Of Communication in his back pocket, he landed in Los Angeles in 2019.
 
You can catch him regularly performing in Hollywood comedy clubs, with his most recent gig opening for the outspoken and hilarious Nikki Glaser.
